Sure, here is a leg day workout suggestion:

Warm-up:
-5-10 minutes of cardio of your choice (treadmill, elliptical, stationary bike)

Main workout:
1. Squats - 3 sets of 8-12 reps 
2. Romanian Deadlifts - 3 sets of 10-12 reps
3. Leg Press - 3 sets of 15-20 reps
4. Walking Lunges - 3 sets of 8-12 reps (each leg)
5. Calf Raises - 3 sets of 15-20 reps

Cool-down:
-5-10 minutes of stretching (focusing on legs and lower back)

*Note: Be sure to choose weights that challenge you, but that also allow you to maintain proper form. Rest for 1-2 minutes between each set.
